            <para>Mounting hardware to be supplied locally.</para>
        </partsinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove old horn bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect old harness at frame rail (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9408061">Figure 1</hotlnk>) and remove from radiator horse collar.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount new horn(s) to inside of front engine mounting crossmember as illustrated in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9408061">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9408062">Figure 2</hotlnk>
                    with 5/16 inch x 1 inch bolt, nut and lock washer (supplied locally). Tighten to 195 to 265 in-lbs.
                    (22 to 30 Nm). There are holes in the crossmember to mount the horn(s) to.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the new harness where the old harness was removed on the driver side frame rail
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9408061">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Route the new harness inside the front engine mounting crossmember. Connect the harness
                    to the horn(s). Clip the harness to the crossmember to secure it firmly in place.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9408062" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g9408062.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Mounting Single/Dual Horns Inside Engine Mounting Crossmember</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
